nutrition:
  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 52 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 790 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/balsamic-fig-sirloin-5d8a1e1b896cd855e64c206d
servings: 2
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash
and dry all produce. Halve @Fingerling Potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise. Strip
@Rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; chop leaves. Halve, peel, and mince
half the @Shallot{1} (mince whole shallot for 4 servings). Slice
@Garlic{2%clove}.

On a #baking sheet{}, toss potatoes with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tbsp},
a pinch of chopped rosemary, @Pepper{}, and a few big pinches of @Salt{}. Roast
on top rack until tender and lightly crisped, ~{20-25%minutes}.

On a second baking sheet, toss @Green Beans{6%ounce} and garlic with a drizzle
of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Once potatoes have roasted for ~{10%minutes},
place green beans on middle rack. Roast until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @Sirloin Steak{14%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season
generously all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of
@Vegetable Oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and
cook until browned but not yet cooked through, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Turn
off heat; wipe out pan. Transfer steak to baking sheet with green beans; roast
until steak is cooked to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes}. (If green beans
finish first, remove from sheet and continue roasting steak.) Set steak aside
to rest.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Stir in
minced shallot and a pinch of remaining chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring, until
fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}. Stir in @water{1/4%cup}, half the
@Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon} (use all for 4), @Beef Stock Concentrate{1}, and
@Fig Jam{2%tablespoon}. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.
Season with salt and pepper.

Slice steak against the grain. Divide between plates with potatoes and green
beans. Top steak with sauce.

